beer.beer_description:
Citra / Mosaic

As you may know, we absolutely love Pilsners. We also love hops and an ABV that sneaks above 8.0%.

It's a style we’ve been excited about brewing from a technical standpoint, but with german pilsner malt, the freshest Citra and Mosaic and a long cold ferment we have our first New World Imperial Pilsner. You could see from Mike and Erik’s faces as they were trying it from the tank that they’re chuffed with how it came out.

Flip your favourite record over and chill out to the B-Side with a B-Side.

items.badge_description: Round and round the wheel goes! Which style you’ll be drinking, nobody knows! Your desire to explore different styles is inspiring. Keep it up! That's a check-in to at least 155 different styles. Try 5 more for Level 32!

When a single isn’t enough, make it a double. Doubling the hops and malts in a recipe results in a higher ABV and can pack quite a boozey punch. That's 95 different beers with the style that contains Imperial / Double in its style name. Try 5 more for Level 20!
